BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 40 608 Td (Chapter 20: Getting Started Checklist) Tj ET
q 0.4 G 1 w 40 600 m 392 600 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 575 Td (Start with just one AI tool - do not try to adopt everything at once.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 553 Td (Choose a health-related goal: better sleep, more exercise, or medication management.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 531 Td (Get a basic smartwatch or fitness tracker as your entry point to AI health tools.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 509 Td (Set up a voice assistant \(Alexa, Google, or Siri\) in your main living space.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 487 Td (Download one health app and use it daily for two weeks before adding more.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 465 Td (Ask a family member or friend to help with initial setup if technology feels overwhelming.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 443 Td (Schedule a telehealth appointment to experience virtual healthcare firsthand.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 421 Td (Join an online community for seniors exploring technology to share tips and encouragement.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 399 Td (Set realistic expectations - AI is a tool to help, not a replacement for human care.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 377 Td (Review your progress monthly and add new tools as you become more comfortable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 40 355 Td (Remember: every expert was once a beginner. You can do this at your own pace.) Tj ET

endstream
